  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Execute daily HR tasks such as managing On-boarding/Off-boarding procedures, conducting staff orientation, and other related responsibilities.</li>\n  <li>Manage employee records and ensure all necessary personal documents are complete.</li>\n  <li>Handle processing of Work Pass, Staff Pass, Access Card, and other required identification cards.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with relevant departments to handle employee movements, contract renewals, confirmations, transfers, promotions, resignations, and related administrative tasks.</li>\n  <li>Adhere to internal Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) and statutory regulations while carrying out HR activities.</li>\n  <li>Address employee inquiries regarding HR matters.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with cross-functional teams to facilitate payroll processing.</li>\n  <li>Prepare HR reports and materials for meetings.</li>\n  <li>Contribute to process improvement projects, events, and other functions.</li>\n  <li>Support HR initiatives.</li>\n  <li>Perform additional duties as assigned by management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Human Resource Management or an equivalent qualification.</li>\n  <li>3 years or more experience in a relevant field.</li>\n  <li>Prior experience in the Human Capital related business is an added advantage.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Office.</li>\n  <li>Detail-oriented with the ability to handle multiple tasks.</li>\n  <li>Highly adaptable to change and possess a positive mindset.</li>\n  <li>Strong team player with excellent communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Independent and confident when interacting with internal and external stakeholders.</li>\n</ul>",
